cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with training a regression network to predict 3D morphable model coordinates from image pixels using only unlabeled photographs. This involves using facial recognition networks and differentiable rendering techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces novel objectives to make training from features feasible and avoid network fooling effects, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of differentiable rendering techniques and morphable models also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multi-view identity loss, which could fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning techniques, which could also suggest the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
